    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dun</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1,
                                    1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 109.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge receipt of yours of
                            the 31st of July, with which was inclosed copy of your instruction to
                            the United States consuls in Japan to use their good offices to protect
                            Chinese subjects in Japan.</p>
                <p>Mr. Gresham’s telegraphic instruction, sent to you on the 29th ultimo and
                            confirmed in mine of the 31st ultimo, will suggest to you the proper
                            limitation to be set to the exercise of the unofficial good offices of
                            our consuls as the representatives of a friendly power and not as
                            charged with Chinese consular functions.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
